<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-16068] Camel-AWS2-S3: Fix condition for throwing exception in case bucket does not exist</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-16068</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Wrong code on line 119:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (ase.awsErrorDetails().errorCode().equalsIgnoreCase(&quot;404&quot;)) &lt;/p&gt;
{
 throw ase;
 }&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Correct writing method:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
if (!ase.awsErrorDetails().errorCode().equalsIgnoreCase(&quot;404&quot;)) {
 throw ase;
 }

&lt;p&gt;There are similar bugs elsewhere&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;camel-aws2-s3:3.7.0&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
